{
  "text": "(3) Mimicking bleeding or haematuria via self-inflicted injury; (4) Creating illness by artificial means (e.g. ingestion of laxatives); (5) Exploiting stable but abnormal biochemical/physiological findings to mimic illness (e.g. abuse of a known electrocardiogram [ECG] abnormality to gain admission for investigation of acute myocardial infarction); [CITATION_1] Tampering with laboratory specimens.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "2002439"
